                "text_GAc7eV": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>STEP 1: This one begins inside to out: two even lengths of lace coming out of the bottom two eyelets and run up vertically over the boot on each side to the eyelet pair above. Don’t cross them over yet <br/><br/>STEP 2: Once you’ve created your two loops on either side, it’s time for the ladder ‘rungs’. Cross the lace lengths over through the corresponding loops you’ve created, then thread them through the eyelets above <br/><br/>STEP 3: Repeat the process on the next four eyelets, tightening as you go, and again until you reach the top. Pair this robust lacing style with a hardy knot inside the boot, and you’re set</p>",
